LAGOS – Virgin Atlantic and Delta Air Lines have renewed their handling contracts with the Nigerian Aviation Handling Company (NAHCO) PLC for their Lagos operations. Also, Air France/Royal Dutch retained its operations in Lagos, Abuja, and Port Harcourt with NAHCO, while Ethiopian Airlines renewed its contracts with the company. Mr. Samuel Akinrinmade, Head, Corporate Communications, NAHCO, in a statement, said that the renewal of the contracts by the two airlines indicated the continuous dominance of the ground handling company in Nigeria. Akinrinmade clarified that Ethiopian Airlines signed a new contract for the provision of warehousing services for its Lagos operations. Besides, the statement hinted that the company has also won the Qatar Airways’ Freighter and warehousing contracts for Kano and Port Harcourt. Recall that NAHCO, which handles most of the foreign airlines operating in the country, had recently announced the signing of Qatar Airways handling for Kano and Port Harcourt. NAHCO currently has an all-encompassing contract with the airline in Lagos and Abuja, providing passenger, cargo, and ramp handling services to Qatar Airways, which also includes the provision of crew transportation and other ancillary services to the respected airliner.